Introducción

Datos descargados de https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/machine-learning-databases/housing/

Leyendo el archivo

library(readr)
library(dplyr)
set.seed(175904)
housing = read.csv2("housing.data", header = FALSE, sep = "", col.names = c("CRIM", "ZN", "INDUS", "CHAS", "NOX", "RM", "AGE", "DIS", "RAD", "TAX", "PTRATIO", "B", "LSTAT", "MEDV"))
housing$id = seq.int(nrow(housing))
housing_l = sample_n(housing, 400) #learning df
housing_t = housing[!(housing$id %in% housing_l$id),] #test df

MEDV utilizando RSS (Residual Sum of Squares)

rss_calc <- function(datos){
  y <- datos$MEDV
  x <- datos$RM
  fun_out <- function(beta){
    y_hat <- beta[1] + beta[2]*x
    e <- (y - y_hat)
    rss <- sum(e^2)
    0.5*rss
  }
  fun_out
}
